706108f.title: Brooklyn: Ocean Avenue - Oriental Boulevard
706108f.text:
Ocean Ave., east side, at the N.W. corner of Oriental Boulevard, show.
ing the entrance to Lloyds Fire Works in front of which was the New York,
Brooklyn and Manhattan Beach R.R.
About 1907.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
706108f.folder: Ocean Avenue & Oriental Boulevard, Brooklyn, NY

706144f-b.title: Brooklyn: Oriental Boulevard - Ocean Avenue
706144f-b.text:
Oriental Boulevard, south side, west of Ocean Ave., showihg the
Manhattan Beach Hotel built by Elbert Snediker in 1877 and owned by
Austin Corbin, who opened it on July 18, 1877. The 4-story west wing
was added in 1876, and it was again enlarged in 1879, Overall, the
hotel was 660 feet long and accomodated 500 people. Its owners or
lessees were H.3. Breslin, 1883; Simieon Leland, 1891; T.F. Silleck,
1809-1901; Alfred T. Amer, 1909-1910; and Jeseph P. Greaves, 1911,when
iwas demolished in the same year. In 1937 the Manhattan Beach Baths
used the site as a parking place for automobiles.
September 20, 1911.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
The same, a close up.
September 20, 1911.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
